HEADWORD: Jettison
<hw>Jet"ti*son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Jetsam</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mar. Law)</fld> <def>The throwing overboard of
goods from necessity, in order to lighten a vessel in danger of
wreck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Jetsam</er>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jetton</ent>⟦br⟧
